translated: Signe, former principal, Gothenburg, born on October 22, 1880 in Stockholm to Henrik W. and Charlotta Eriksson. Elementary school teacher, graduated in 1902, graduated from teacher's seminary in 1906. Elementary school teacher in Gothenburg from 1902 to 1917, regular subject teacher at Gothenburg's practical intermediate school from 1917 to 1945, principal there from 1917 to 1924, part-time teacher at Gothenburg's school kitchen seminary from 1914 to 1918, same at Gothenburg's city elementary school seminary from 1916 to 1932, principal there from 1924 to 1932 (seminary closed). Member of the Gothenburg general elementary school board since 1923 and board member of several educational associations. Studied in Norway, Denmark, Germany, Austria, Italy, and the USA. Married to Johannes, pastor in Höreda, born on February 25, 1893 in Rumskulla, Kalmar län, son of clergyman A. P. W. and Matilda Sofia W., married in 1925 to Stina Palemona, born Lindgren. Children: Britta born in 1926, Anna-Stina in 1928, Ulla in 1929, Kerstin in 1936. Studied in Linköping, graduated in 1912, Bachelor of Arts in 1915, Bachelor of Theology, practical theological examination, and ordained as a priest from the Linköping diocese in 1921. Assistant curate in Norra Solberga, curate in Järeda from 1922, pastor in Höreda from 1925.
